### -----------------------
### PUBLIC ROUTES (No Token Needed)
### -----------------------

### 1. Get All Teams
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/teams

### 2. Get Team Leaderboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/leaderboard

### 3. Search Teams
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/search?q=hello

### 4. Get Team By Name (Replace 'MyTeamName' with a real team name)
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/MyTeamName

### 5. Get Team Members (Replace 'MyTeamName' with a real team name)
GET {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/MyTeamName/members

### 6. Get User Leaderboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/leaderboard

### 7. Search Users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/search?q=John

### 8. Get Specific User Profile (Replace :id with real User ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_HERE


### -----------------------
### AUTHENTICATED ROUTES (Token Required)
### -----------------------
# To get a token, you usually need to log in via the Frontend.
# For testing, you can grab the 'access_token' from the Network tab in your browser
# after logging into your app, or generate one from the Auth0 Dashboard.

### 9. Sync User (Simulate Login)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/sync
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 10. Get My Profile (Dashboard)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Update My Profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "bio": "I am paddling for a cause!",
    "name": "Ericccc"
}

### 12. Create Team
POST {{baseUrl}}/registrations/team
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "teamName": "The Wave Riders",
    "division": "Community"
}

### 13. Join Team
POST {{baseUrl}}/registrations/join
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "inviteCode": "INVITE_CODE_HERE"
}

### 14. Leave Team
POST {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/leave
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 15. Update Team (Captain Only) - Replace :id with Team ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/TEAM_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "description": "We are the champions",
    "division": "Corporate"
}

### 16. Remove Member (Captain Only) - Replace :id (Team) and :userId (Member)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/TEAM_ID_HERE/members/USER_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 17. Delete Team (Captain Only) - Replace :id with Team ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/public/teams/TEAM_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
